cz.cuni.mff.kocur.base

Class GraphicResources

  • java.lang.Object
    • cz.cuni.mff.kocur.base.GraphicResources

  • public class GraphicResources
extends Object
    This class contains all the graphic resources like images, icons .., that I might need. This is helpful because I don't need to load them each time I need them. Also they might be shared (e. g. icons for buttons). I am not loading everything - I am using hash maps to load icons only at the time they are used.
    Author:
    kocur

      • setLabelIcon

        public static void setLabelIcon(JLabel label,
                                ImageIcon icon)
        Sets the icon for the given label and sets it's text to empty. This comes in handy if you have defined label with initial text and you want it to only the icon in case it has loaded.
        Parameters:
        label - Label that should have the icon set.
        icon - ImageIcon that we are setting to the passed label.

      • setButtonIcon

        public static void setButtonIcon(JButton bttn,
                                 ImageIcon icon)
        Sets the icon for the given button and sets the text to empty. This comes in handy if you have defined button with initial text and you want it to disappear only in case its icon was loaded.
        Parameters:
        bttn - Button that we are setting the icon to.
        icon - Icon you want to set. (preferably one of the static icons referenced inside this class)
